pd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined` are clearly aligned to the definition:\\n\\n- **Identity**: `s_site_id` (site code), `s_site_name`\\n- **Geo**: `s_site_latitude`, `s_site_longitude`, plus `s_city`, `s_state`, `s_zip`, `s_address`\\n- **Market assignment**: `m_market`, `m_area`, `rgn_region` (and also `region` is present\\u2014looks duplicative)\\n- **Physical attributes**: `s_site_type`, `s_site_class`, `s_structure_height_in_feet`, `s_highest_appurtenance_in_feet`, `s_rad_center_agl_in_feet`\\n- **Readiness / blockers / scope flags** (examples present in sample):  \\n  - backhaul/AAV: `pj_aav_telco_ready_status`, `s_aav_eligibility_status_salesforce`, `s_primary_aav_vendor_name_salesforce`, `pj_backhaul_task_selection`  \\n  - access: `s_24x7_site_access`, `s_facility_access_*`, `s_site_access_details`  \\n  - lift/crane / split: `is_lift_required`, `scoping_package_crane_required`, `confirm_split_spo`  \\n  - power proxy: I see provider fields (`s_power_provider_company_name`) but not a clean `power_status`; may be embedded elsewhere in the `pj_*` milestone/status fields.\\n\\nOne interesting data-quality thing: there are **two region-like fields** (`rgn_region` and `region`). We should standardize on one for the node mapping (I\\u2019d default to `rgn_region` since it looks like the structured source, but we can confirm with a quick distinct-count check later).\\n\\nIf you\\u2019re good with it, I\\u2019ll change the mapping\\u2019s SQL template to only return these relevant columns (still keyed by `s_site_id`, labeled by `s_site_name`).", "timestamp": "2026-03-05T13:11:44.459758+00:00", "updates_applied": ["sql_template", "reasoning_summary", "sample_data"]}], "contract": {"function_name": "get_site", "node_type": "core", "node_id": "site", "node_label": "Site", "description": "Query Site data from stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined", "parameters": [{"name": "s_site_id\\" AS \\"site_code", "type": "string", "description": "Filter by s_site_id\\" AS \\"site_code"