igned to a site/project\\u201d.  \\n   - **Edge alignment:** directly supports Site and Market context in the same row.\\n\\n3) **`stg_tmo_rejections_master_file`**  \\n   - **Why it\\u2019s a candidate:** it includes a column that *looks like* \\u201creviewed company\\u201d tied to CW quality media checklist: `trmf_ms_1553_cw_quality_media_cl_reviewed_company` (often this is the GC/vendor being reviewed/rejected).  \\n   - **When to use:** if you want \\u201cGC\\u201d specifically in the context of **quality/rejections/SLA breaches** rather than assignment.  \\n   - **Edge alignment:** weaker for \\u201cassigned to site\\u201d unless it also carries reliable site identifiers (`trmf_site_code`) + consistent vendor naming.\\n\\n4) **NDPC / NAS operational tables (secondary candidates)**  \\n   These are *less likely* to be \\u201cGeneral Contractor\\u201d sources, but sometimes store \\u201ccompany/vendor\\u201d in free text:\\n   - `stg_services_ndpc_sessions_daily_from_sdb`\\n   - `stg_services_ndpc_answers_daily_from_sdb`\\n   - `stg_tmo_nas_daily_dashboard`, `stg_nas_*` tables  \\n   **When to use:** only if we discover contractor/vendor fields inside them (not obvious from the abbreviated column lists).\\n\\nTo make this concrete, I\\u2019d like to quickly check how \\u201cGC-like\\u201d values appear across the two MBT tables (macro vs forecast), including whether `construction_gc` exists only in macro.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nIf you tell me which \\u201cflavor\\u201d you intend for this node, we can lock the mapping:\\n- **Planned/forecast GC** \\u2192 likely `stg_ndpd_mbt_combine_site_wise_forecast`\\n- **Actual assigned/executing GC** \\u2192 keep `stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined`\\n- **Quality/rejection-attributed vendor** \\u2192 consider `stg_tmo_rejections_master_file` (and adjust edges accordingly)\\n\\n**Query Results (SELECT \\n  \'stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined\' AS table_nam...):**\\n```\\n[\\n  {\\n    \\"table_name\\": \\"stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_ma